Rust equivalents found:
  - emCrossPtr<T> -> Weak<T> (std::rc::Weak)
    - emContext.rs:40: parent: Option<Weak<emContext>> (parent reference)
    - emContext.rs:41: children: RefCell<Vec<Weak<emContext>>> (child references)
  - emCrossPtrList -> no explicit equivalent; Weak references don't need a list on the target side
    - Rc/Weak handles automatic invalidation: when the Rc is dropped, all Weak references
      return None on upgrade(), which is the same semantic as BreakCrossPtrs nullifying all pointers
  - No search results for CrossPtrList, BreakCrossPtrs, or LinkCrossPtr in Rust codebase

Coverage gaps:
  - emCrossPtrList::BreakCrossPtrs(): no explicit equivalent; Weak::upgrade() returns None after Rc drop
  - emCrossPtrList::LinkCrossPtr(): no equivalent needed; Rc::downgrade() creates Weak without registering
  - emCrossPtr copy semantics (copy constructs a new weak ref to same object): Weak::clone() in Rust
  - emBorder PanelPointerCache: not verified whether Rust emBorder uses Weak for this
  - emFileDialog OverwriteDialog: not verified in Rust

OPEN QUESTIONS:
  - The C++ pattern allows early invalidation via BreakCrossPtrs() in destructors before full cleanup; Rust's Weak only invalidates when the last Rc drops. Is this timing difference significant for any emCore code path?
  - emBorder's PanelPointerCache and emFileDialog's OverwriteDialog: are these ported with Weak references or with a different pattern?

