================================================================================
REVIEWED SUMMARY (reviewed — unverified items marked NOT VERIFIED)
================================================================================

C++ emCrossPtr.h: weak pointer with explicit invalidation via linked list.

21 files outside emCore use this type.

C++ provides:
  emCrossPtr<T>    — weak pointer that auto-nullifies when target calls
                     BreakCrossPtrs(). Implemented as intrusive linked list.
  emCrossPtrList   — list embedded in the target object. Destructor calls
                     BreakCrossPtrs() to nullify all pointers to the target.

Rust equivalent (verified):
  emCrossPtr<T>    -> Weak<T> (std::rc::Weak)
    emContext.rs:40  — parent: Option<Weak<emContext>>
    emContext.rs:41  — children: RefCell<Vec<Weak<emContext>>>
  emCrossPtrList   -> no equivalent. Weak doesn't need a list on the target
                     side; Weak::upgrade() returns None after Rc drops.

No Rust equivalent exists for:
  BreakCrossPtrs() — explicit early invalidation.
  LinkCrossPtr()   — explicit registration of pointer with target.

Open question 1 investigated: "Is the BreakCrossPtrs timing difference significant?"
  C++ calls BreakCrossPtrs() early in destructors, before other cleanup:
    emContext.cpp:48  — before deleting child contexts
    emView.cpp:107    — before deleting root panel and view input filters
    emWindow.cpp:68   — before deleting child windows
  This means cross pointers become NULL while the target is still
  partially alive. In Rust, Weak::upgrade() returns None only after
  the last Rc drops, which is after all cleanup.
  If any code checks a cross pointer during the target's destruction
  sequence (between BreakCrossPtrs and full destruction), the C++ code
  sees NULL but Rust's Weak::upgrade() would still succeed.
  NOT VERIFIED: whether any code actually does this.

Open question 2 investigated: "Are PanelPointerCache and OverwriteDialog ported?"
  emBorder.rs: no reference to PanelPointerCache, Weak, or Rc (verified
    by grep). The C++ emBorder.h:410 member emCrossPtr<emPanel>
    PanelPointerCache has no Rust counterpart.
  emFileDialog.rs: no reference to OverwriteDialog or Weak (verified
    by grep). The C++ emFileDialog.h:204 member emCrossPtr<emDialog>
    OverwriteDialog has no Rust counterpart. emFileDialog.rs uses
    Rc only for emLook (line 48).
  Both are concrete gaps — C++ cross-pointer members with no Rust equivalent.
